<subSubSection pageNumber="788" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="788">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="788">Note:</emphasis>
Jonsell (in Humbert, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="788">Fl. Madagascar</emphasis>
84: 8. 1982) typified the name with 846.1 (LINN). However, the absence of a root (necessary to apply infraspecific nomenclature) caused Pistrick &amp; Jarvis (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="788">Feddes Repert.</emphasis>
98: 477. 1987) to reject 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jonsell’s">Jonsell's</normalizedToken>
choice in favour of a more complete collection in 
<specimenReference collectionCode="UPS">
Herb. Burser (
<collectionCode>UPS</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
. Under Art. 9.17, however, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jonsell’s">Jonsell's</normalizedToken>
choice of 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
must stand but Pistrick &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jarvis’">Jarvis'</normalizedToken>
choice of the Burser material as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, is correctable to an 
<typeStatus>epitype</typeStatus>
(Art. 9.8).
</paragraph>
